result.execSummary:
The defendant Dean W Roundy was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Original Warrant has been received and destroyed
Warrant was canceled.  Talked to Laura N at GLSO.
from Clerk to Defendant re: Court-ordered Payment Arrangements

1:03 p.m.  Defendant appears without counsel.
Defendant makes statement.  
Court orders warrant - stayed upon payment of $25.00 today and by the end of each month thereafter.  Failure to make payments will result in warrant.
Court adjourned 1:04 p.m.
Amended Payment Plan Agreement/Letter of Understanding

8:46 a.m.  Defendant present in court without counsel.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  DA recites agreement - upon plea to the charge will recommend court costs.  Defendant concurs.  Court goes over right to counsel.  Defendant waives right to counsel.  Court accepts waiver.

Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation.

Defendant enters a plea of GUILTY.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty on count 1 as charged.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  Sentencing statement by DA.  No statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to:  

-Court costs.  Court grants the defendant 60 days to pay or payment plan.  Court orders cash bond be applied.    
-Defendant is to submit a DNA Sample.

Court adjourned at 8:51 a.m.

8:51 a.m.  Defendant present in court without counsel.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant confirms receipt of the criminal complaint and waives reading.  Court instructs the defendant of the maximum penalty on each count.  Court finds probable cause.  Court instructs the defendant of his right to an attorney.  Defendant enters a plea of NOT GUILTY.  Court goes over right to counsel.  Defendant waives right to counsel.  Court accepts waiver.  DA makes bond recommendation.  Court sets bond at $100.00 cash bond to continue.  Court will set for Status Hearing on November 16, 2015 at 8:45 a.m.  Defendant to make appointment wih the DA.

Court adjourned at 8:54 a.m.
